# SECURITY RULES

> Security is not optional, it's a requirement. These rules are MANDATORY.

---

## CRITICAL — NEVER DO

```typescript
// ❌ NEVER — secrets in code
const API_KEY = 'sk_live_abc123';

// ❌ NEVER — SQL injection
const query = `SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ${userId}`;

// ❌ NEVER — eval
eval(userInput);

// ❌ NEVER — disable security
app.use(cors({ origin: '*' }));

// ❌ NEVER — log secrets
console.log('Password:', password);
```

---

## AUTHENTICATION

- Use NextAuth for auth (already configured)
- Passwords hashed with bcryptjs (project uses bcryptjs)
- Secure cookies: httpOnly, secure, sameSite
- Short-lived sessions

---

## INPUT VALIDATION

- Validate ALL input with Zod schemas
- Sanitize user input (trim, remove HTML)
- Limit request body size
- Validate file uploads: type, size, rename

---

## SECRETS

- All secrets in `.env.local` (gitignored)
- `.env.example` with placeholder values
- Generate strong secrets: `openssl rand -base64 32`
- Validate env variables at startup with Zod

---

## LOGGING

```typescript
// ✅ Log safe data
logger.info('User logged in', { userId: user.id });

// ❌ NEVER log
logger.info('Login', { email, password });  // password!
logger.debug('Token', { accessToken });     // token!
```

---

## CHECKLIST

- [ ] All secrets in env variables
- [ ] `.env.local` in `.gitignore`
- [ ] Input validation on all API routes
- [ ] Passwords hashed (bcryptjs)
- [ ] No secrets in logs
- [ ] SQL injection protection (Prisma)
- [ ] File uploads validated (type + size)

